channel.title: Latest News and News Headlines | Daily Telegraph

item.title: PM breaks silence on Biden’s name error
item.description: Prime Minister Scott Morrison has laughed off US President Joe Biden appearing to forget his name at a major international announcement.

item.title: Mates’ shock act after teen’s 9m fall
item.description: A teenager who suffered critical injuries in a Gold Coast balcony fall was initially dragged back upstairs by his mates, with a neighbour having to step in to call an ambulance after 45 minutes.

item.title: 10km traffic jam after horror M4 crash
item.description: A truck crash on the M4 has caused traffic chaos for commuters travelling into the city from western Sydney.

item.title: US reassures livid France after Australia scraps submarine deal
item.description: The United States on Thursday struggled to contain the fallout after France furiously protested Australia's scrapping of a major arms deal in favor of US nuclear submarines.

item.title: Brazil turns the tide with Covid-19 vaccines
item.description: Despite a slow start plagued by much controversy that still haunts President Jair Bolsonaro, Brazil's coronavirus vaccination campaign is now one of the fastest-paced and farthest-reaching in the world.

item.title: Hundreds strike at Aussie Cadbury factory
item.description: Hundreds of Cadbury workers in Melbourne are set to go on strike to call for the international sweets giant to give them job security and better pay and conditions.

item.title: Man in hospital with Covid for 399 days
item.description: A Covid-19 patient who spent more than a year recovering in a Sydney hospital has urged people not to wait and get vaccinated now.

item.title: Aussie swim star’s ‘nightmare’ finally over
item.description: Shayna Jack is free to continue her competitive swimming career after the Court of Arbitration for Sport dismissed the World Anti-Doping Agency (WADA) and Sport Integrity Australia’s (SIA) appeal in her doping case.

item.title: Biden says huge spending plan can redefine US ‘trajectory’
item.description: President Joe Biden said Thursday he is confident Congress will pass a mammoth middle class spending plan that can "change the trajectory" of the United States.

item.title: French forces kill Islamic State’s boss in Sahel
item.description: France said Thursday that its troops deployed in Africa's Sahel region had killed the head of the Islamic State in the Greater Sahara, who had been hunted for years over deadly attacks on US soldiers and French aid workers.
